[src:miranda-language/referential-transparency] The first position is also purely referential for the same substitutivity reason.
[src:miranda-language/referential-transparency] Indeed, the first position is not purely referential in the statement because substituting *The capital of the United Kingdom* for *London* changes the value of the statement and the quotation.
[src:miranda-language/referential-transparency] So in the first position, the ‘_ contains _’ and quote operators destroy the relation between an expression and the value that it denotes.
[src:miranda-language/referential-transparency] ‘London’ refers to the largest city of the United Kingdom.
